full_text: Screened by NARA, 7/24/2023 U.S. Departmen. Justice Immigration and Naturalization Service California Service Center P.O. Box 10400 Laguna Niguel, CA 92607-0400 Date: Dec. 10, 2001 Josefa Matilde Romano 363 Avenida Manzanos San Jose, CA 95123 Refer to file no.: A 073 964 564 REQUEST TO WAIVE REQUIRED FILING FEE FOR FORM N-400 APPLICATION FOR JOSEFA MATILDE ROMANO: Upon review of your fee waiver request, the INS has determined that you have not demonstrated an "inability to pay" the required filing fee for the above noted application or petition because: Your household income does not appear to be at or below the Federal Poverty Guidelines and/or you have not demonstrated that you have (within the last 180 days) qualified for or received a "federal means-tested public benefit." You have not demonstrated any extenuating circumstances, including but not limited to being elderly (age 65 or older at the time the fee waiver request was submitted), disabled, unusual individual or household expenditures, and/or humanitarian or compassionate reasons that would justify granting your fee waiver request. Due to insufficient information and supporting documentation contained in your fee waiver request, the INS was not able to determine your "inability to pay" the required filing fee. ACCORDINGLY, YOUR FEE WAIVER REQUEST IS HEREBY DENIED. Donald W. Neufeld Acting Director Enclosures: Form N-400 & Application for Fee Waiver CSC11065/WS14052/DIV IV
